The paper discusses the application of Differential Power Analysis (DPA) attacks and countermeasures on neural network classifiers, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel hardware design for implementing the countermeasures, which could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), computer architecture (cs.AR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
